We have been experiencing blue-green algae (non-toxic) this summer.  Lake levels  are very low.
Sunny and calm.  Many people on the lake today.
Heavy rain has caused water level to rise and run off has impaired lake clarity.
Cool- cle- sunny weather.  Slight west wind- air temperature about 73 degrees.
Sunny- 74 degrees and a slight breeze.
Partly cloudy- 65 degrees with a slight breeze.  Lake level is very high.
Sunny- warm- 78 degrees.  Lake is very calm.
Beautiful sunny day after a strong wind storm on Saturday that took down many trees in the area.
Partly cloudy day. Slight breeze- about 72 degrees.  Lake level is still high and trees affected/dying from standing in water.
Lake water is very high. Water level very high.  Saw 2 double crested cormorants on the lake.
Lake level has been extremely high due to excessive rain.
Sunset Lake continues to rise to extreme levels.  Trees are beginning to fall into the water and as you scan the shoreline many pine trees display brown colors due to decline.
